1
00:02:22,719 --> 00:02:23,640
Hello.

2
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:26,000
How are you?

3
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:33,160
Are you going behind the bridge?

4
00:02:33,879 --> 00:02:35,600
This bridge or the next one?

5
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:38,720
The next one, thank you.

6
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:57,360
Thank you.

7
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:12,560
What's that?

8
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:16,880
What you have mounted there.

9
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:21,040
This?

10
00:03:21,639 --> 00:03:23,240
Is it an anti-theft device?

11
00:03:23,759 --> 00:03:25,360
You could say that.

12
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:28,920
It looks like a fine piece of equipment.

13
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:32,240
Do you recognize it?

14
00:03:33,159 --> 00:03:35,120
I'ts somewhat my department.

15
00:03:36,159 --> 00:03:40,360
If I may say so,
it's a good idea to secure your vehicle.

16
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:44,800
I have a cousin, and the other day...
He had no idea what'd happened to him!

17
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,280
He goes out to work,

18
00:03:47,479 --> 00:03:52,280
he sees that someone stole his wheels
and placed bricks instead!

19
00:03:52,479 --> 00:03:53,400
What, which vehicle?

20
00:03:53,599 --> 00:03:57,320
A Kia Pride, the poor guy!
Stealing the wheels of a caddy.

21
00:03:57,759 --> 00:04:00,080
If I was this country's ruler,

22
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:04,200
I'd hang one or two 
to calm the others

23
00:04:04,719 --> 00:04:10,160
Hang them? And then what?
You're being a bit harsh.

24
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:15,160
Perhaps this person only did
this out of necessity.

25
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:17,120
What if he simply must've, do you hear!

26
00:04:17,319 --> 00:04:20,160
Which necessity?
What are you talking about?

27
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:21,920
Perhaps he was in desperate need.

28
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:25,680
And those who get screwed by his stealing,
Aren't they in need?

29
00:04:25,879 --> 00:04:27,520
What about me!

30
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:30,880
Is it a reason to steal from others
when you're broke?

31
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:32,880
She's funny!

32
00:04:33,079 --> 00:04:35,600
If it happened to you,
what would you do?

33
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:37,360
Would you love it?

34
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:41,360
No, of course not!
I wouldn't like it if it happened to me.

35
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:44,640
But killing people is never
a solution.

36
00:04:44,839 --> 00:04:48,320
I think you should look for the
roots of this misbehaving.

37
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:51,000
Alright, I said one or two...

38
00:04:51,199 --> 00:04:53,200
We're not born criminals.

39
00:04:53,399 --> 00:04:55,240
What're you trying to say?

40
00:04:55,439 --> 00:04:59,800
If you lay down one or two,
the others will step in line.

41
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:02,840
I see, but you're wrong.

42
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:06,960
A crime occurs by an
interaction of circumstances.

43
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:09,520
Killing someone for stealing some wheels!

44
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:11,760
Do you realize what you're saying?

45
00:05:11,959 --> 00:05:14,640
Recently, two guys were hung.

46
00:05:14,839 --> 00:05:17,400
For less than that.

47
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:20,600
A few people more or less doesn't matter.

48
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:22,080
You shild think carefully.

49
00:05:22,279 --> 00:05:24,640
You don't have the slightest clue.

50
00:05:24,839 --> 00:05:26,520
I know very well...

51
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:30,000
There have been hangings
for a racketeering fraud recently...

52
00:05:30,199 --> 00:05:33,360
And what did it change?

53
00:05:33,560 --> 00:05:35,640
I don't understand you, lady.

54
00:05:35,839 --> 00:05:38,240
It didn't solve anything.

55
00:05:38,439 --> 00:05:41,960
Lady, it's the law and the sharia
who decide on that.

56
00:05:42,319 --> 00:05:46,600
If it hasn't been resolved then,
it must be because

57
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:48,960
the law hasn't been applied well enough.

58
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:51,760
So, you're all pumped up about nothing.

59
00:05:51,959 --> 00:05:55,200
According to you, to fully implement the law

60
00:05:55,399 --> 00:05:58,280
we have to argue
the number of executions?

61
00:05:58,480 --> 00:06:03,040
We already have the world record
of hangings after China!

62
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:06,160
Have we learned our lesson?
I'm sure we have not.

63
00:06:06,360 --> 00:06:09,160
I think you're quite a mouthful.

64
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:11,680
And you should do as I say
a little more often

65
00:06:11,879 --> 00:06:13,560
The Parsian hospital, which direction is it?

66
00:06:13,759 --> 00:06:15,280
Straight ahead.

67
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:17,200
Or you'll fall behind.

68
00:06:17,399 --> 00:06:22,040
What do you mean, straight ahead?
The Parsian hospital, that's on Sadaat Abad.

69
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:24,560
Between Kaj and Farhang.

70
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:26,280
Do I turn around?

71
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:28,880
Yes, you have to go to Sadaat Abad.

72
00:06:29,879 --> 00:06:30,760
Okay, fine.

73
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:33,960
Have you gotten it with a Kinder Surprise,
your license?

74
00:06:34,279 --> 00:06:35,760
Why?

75
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:38,040
Is it your taxi or what?

76
00:06:38,759 --> 00:06:44,600
Faut le faire pour pas savoir
où est l'hôpital Parsian.
You don't even know how to
get to the Parsian hospital.

77
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:46,360
I always go straight ahead.

78
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:49,200
Are you sure you haven't
tricked us by any chance?

79
00:06:49,399 --> 00:06:51,160
We walk there.

80
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:52,600
What's the story?

81
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:56,360
I understand well, 
but since we're having this discussion

82
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:59,120
I would like to ask you a question.

83
00:06:59,319 --> 00:07:00,400
I'm listening

84
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:02,040
What is your job?

85
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:05,240
I don't see the connection.

86
00:07:05,439 --> 00:07:06,760
Oh, but there is a connection;

87
00:07:06,959 --> 00:07:10,440
Quand on défend une idée,
c'est soit par conviction,
When you're defending an idea,
it's out of belief...

88
00:07:10,639 --> 00:07:12,080
Or a particular interest.

89
00:07:12,399 --> 00:07:15,000
I would like to know
what your profession is.

90
00:07:15,279 --> 00:07:18,480
And you? Interrogations aside,
what do you do?

91
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:20,080
If I tell you, will you tell me?

92
00:07:20,279 --> 00:07:23,160
Sure, we'll see.

93
00:07:23,439 --> 00:07:24,840
I am a teacher.

94
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:29,480
Come on, no kidding!

95
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:31,520
Probably like Mary Poppins,

96
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:33,720
Spending her time

97
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:35,960
keeping some brats busy

98
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:38,840
with entertainment.

99
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:42,600
I'd bet on that, anyway.

100
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:44,800
Fine! Now it's your turn.

101
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:47,160
I'm independent.

102
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:49,320
I'm going to tell you
in which branch I'm working...

103
00:07:49,759 --> 00:07:52,960
Wait, I have to get out right here.

104
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:54,920
What do I owe you?

105
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:56,360
Nothing, it's fine.

106
00:07:58,680 --> 00:07:59,560
Definitely...

107
00:07:59,759 --> 00:08:02,520
You're definitely no taxi driver.

108
00:08:02,959 --> 00:08:05,440
I've figured you out multiple times now.

109
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:09,280
Independent or not,
you must perform an activity.

110
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:12,000
I'm going to get out, then I'll tell you.

111
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:15,520
Do you want the truth, little lady?

112
00:08:16,079 --> 00:08:16,760
Yes.

113
00:08:16,959 --> 00:08:19,000
My specialty is pickpocketing.

114
00:08:19,199 --> 00:08:20,200
Pickpocketing?

115
00:08:20,399 --> 00:08:21,240
Yes.

116
00:08:21,439 --> 00:08:26,040
But I don't steal from professors like
you, or from taxis like these guys.

117
00:08:26,439 --> 00:08:30,160
It's those who have fallen so far they
steal tires from underneath a Pride,

118
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:34,360
they cannot fall any lower,
they are less than nothing.

119
00:08:34,559 --> 00:08:37,880
Also, an advice!
Stop crying for them.

120
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:39,840
Good luck.

121
00:08:40,159 --> 00:08:41,480
Unbelievable.

122
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:43,640
Where does he get off, that one?

123
00:08:49,519 --> 00:08:50,840
Hello, how are you?

124
00:08:51,039 --> 00:08:53,680
I'm arriving in ten minutes.

125
00:08:54,399 --> 00:08:55,800
Yes, ten minutes.

126
00:08:56,039 --> 00:08:58,280
I'm going to get out over there.

127
00:08:59,679 --> 00:09:00,560
Here is fine?

128
00:09:00,759 --> 00:09:01,720
Yes, thank you.

129
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:05,640
There you are.

130
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:07,280
Thank you.

131
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:27,400
Thank you for not taking
another passenger.

132
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:29,440
- Can I get in?
- I'm sorry.

133
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:40,760
M. Panahi, I've recognized you!

134
00:09:42,919 --> 00:09:45,400
Regardless of the hat.

135
00:09:47,919 --> 00:09:50,600
Do you mind if I come sit in the front?

136
00:09:52,399 --> 00:09:53,520
Sure.

137
00:10:10,879 --> 00:10:12,240
Thank you very much.

138
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:20,240
You're doing a film, right?

139
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:23,000
That man and that woman...

140
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:27,400
Can you take that one?
Thank you, to Shahran please.

141
00:10:28,799 --> 00:10:30,760
They were actors, right?

142
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:33,040
Do you know how I figured it out?

143
00:10:33,240 --> 00:10:36,760
That last thing he said was very much like

144
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:39,640
that sequence in the café from "Sang et Or"

145
00:10:40,799 --> 00:10:43,720
You, a taxi driver?
Don't fool me. 

146
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:45,520
It's a job like any other.

147
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:49,320
It is, but it's not your job.

148
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:53,960
Don't you recognize me?

149
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:58,360
I seem to have forgotten.

150
00:10:59,080 --> 00:11:00,680
It's me, Omid.

151
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:02,160
Omid who?

152
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:05,320
Omid, the film delivery guy!

153
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:08,200
I delivered those DVD's to you!

154
00:11:08,399 --> 00:11:10,640
To your son, to be precise.

155
00:11:11,159 --> 00:11:13,920
More than once even, you were there.

156
00:11:14,159 --> 00:11:18,960
I asked you how you were doing.
You said: "I'm fine, lad."

157
00:11:19,159 --> 00:11:22,400
You asked me to get you
Once Upon A Time In Anatolia.

158
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:24,640
No sooner said than done.

159
00:11:25,559 --> 00:11:27,800
Why are you sweating so much?

160
00:11:29,559 --> 00:11:30,840
It's very hot.

161
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:33,480
Guess which other film you wanted.

162
00:11:36,759 --> 00:11:37,520
I don't recall.

163
00:11:37,720 --> 00:11:40,600
Midnight in Paris, from Woody Allen.

164
00:11:40,799 --> 00:11:42,880
- Ah, that was you.
- Absolutely!

165
00:11:56,759 --> 00:11:58,760
It's not out yet, this one.

166
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:01,280
And that isn't even everything...

167
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:06,200
I can get even get you footage
from ungoing productions.

168
00:12:18,399 --> 00:12:19,560
Hello. I'll call you back.

169
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:28,440
Open the door!

170
00:12:31,080 --> 00:12:33,240
Hospital Chamran.

171
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:35,840
No, you can better go to Milad.

172
00:12:36,039 --> 00:12:37,880
He doesn't have any money, the poor guy.

173
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:42,440
Where is it? How should we drive?

174
00:12:46,120 --> 00:12:48,000
Go quickly, please!

175
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:49,240
What happened?

176
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:50,840
There's been an accident.

177
00:12:51,039 --> 00:12:52,960
I'm dying...

178
00:12:53,159 --> 00:12:54,960
A motorcycle accident.

179
00:12:58,440 --> 00:13:00,160
It's not my fault.

180
00:13:00,360 --> 00:13:03,240
I told you to keep your helmet on.

181
00:13:04,639 --> 00:13:05,920
Paper, please...

182
00:13:10,759 --> 00:13:14,120
Not a paper towel,
some paper so I can write my will.

183
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:22,040
Driver, take some paper and 
write down what I tell you.

184
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:24,120
What does he want?

185
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:26,240
Write down what I tell you.

186
00:13:26,960 --> 00:13:28,920
My wife doesn't understand.

187
00:13:29,120 --> 00:13:31,640
According to the law,
she will inherit nothing.

188
00:13:32,480 --> 00:13:35,520
A few turkeys at most.

189
00:13:35,799 --> 00:13:37,600
She'll end up on the street.

190
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:43,520
Hurry up, please.

191
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:46,080
A mobile phone, do you have one?

192
00:13:48,399 --> 00:13:50,360
No, not to make a phonecall. 

193
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:52,120
I want the camera.

194
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:54,320
On me.

195
00:13:54,519 --> 00:13:56,200
I don't any battery left.

196
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:05,480
The camera...

197
00:14:08,639 --> 00:14:09,880
Turn it towards me.

198
00:14:12,159 --> 00:14:13,520
Film me.

199
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:15,760
In the name of the great Allah...

200
00:14:16,519 --> 00:14:19,040
I am Mohammad Rabei,

201
00:14:19,399 --> 00:14:21,320
born in Ramhormoz.

202
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:25,640
ID card number 508,

203
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:27,960
Issued in the same city.

204
00:14:28,159 --> 00:14:31,640
Stop crying, they can't hear me like this.

205
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:33,440
Son of Amin,

206
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:37,240
Healthy in body and mind, 
I leave to my wife

207
00:14:37,559 --> 00:14:40,840
My house at Ghale Hassan Khan,

208
00:14:41,039 --> 00:14:44,800
Bahar, rue Izadi, number 34,

209
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:48,160
and all my possesions.

210
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:52,600
May God forgive me.

211
00:14:53,039 --> 00:14:56,680
I ask of all my brothers,
to leave my wife alone.

212
00:14:57,519 --> 00:14:59,720
Do not conspire against her,

213
00:15:00,279 --> 00:15:03,560
and respect my final wish

214
00:15:03,759 --> 00:15:06,040
To leave her alone.

215
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:07,680
This will...

216
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:11,640
must not fall into their hands.

217
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:13,920
Let her guard it.

218
00:15:14,639 --> 00:15:18,320
There is no other God than Allah.

219
00:15:49,159 --> 00:15:50,720
Get him out.

220
00:15:53,519 --> 00:15:55,160
Help me, hold there.

221
00:16:18,960 --> 00:16:21,320
It's not worth it, take leave!

222
00:16:39,399 --> 00:16:40,880
Wait.

223
00:16:41,639 --> 00:16:46,080
Give me the will please, mister.

224
00:16:46,279 --> 00:16:48,400
I will give it to you later.

225
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:53,240
Take my card, call me.

226
00:16:53,759 --> 00:16:57,200
The ambulance is here, let's go.

227
00:17:09,759 --> 00:17:10,760
There.

228
00:17:13,319 --> 00:17:14,400
He's dead?

229
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:17,560
He'll be fine, it was mostly fear.

230
00:17:18,319 --> 00:17:20,320
He was looking really bad.

231
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:23,880
His eyes were closed.

232
00:17:34,359 --> 00:17:35,400
Yes, it's me.

233
00:17:36,079 --> 00:17:37,120
Is it you?

234
00:17:37,799 --> 00:17:39,040
No, madam.

235
00:17:39,240 --> 00:17:42,120
Rest assured, this is my real number.

236
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:45,200
Of course.

237
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:49,040
I'll call you as soon as possible.

238
00:17:50,759 --> 00:17:51,920
Goodbye.

239
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:55,680
Was that her?

240
00:17:57,319 --> 00:17:58,800
The husband died?

241
00:17:59,279 --> 00:18:01,120
She wanted some certainty.

242
00:18:01,319 --> 00:18:04,080
She was verifying if this
was really my phone number.

243
00:18:05,559 --> 00:18:11,040
You believe I really don't realize
that was all staged, do you?

244
00:18:16,240 --> 00:18:17,960
An empty battery.

245
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:21,480
Can I use your phone?

246
00:18:22,319 --> 00:18:23,400
Thank you.

247
00:18:23,599 --> 00:18:25,560
I'll unlock it.

248
00:18:33,359 --> 00:18:36,240
Hello, I'll be there in ten minutes.

249
00:18:36,440 --> 00:18:40,280
I assure you. Something'd come up.

250
00:18:40,799 --> 00:18:44,160
I know, but this time it's true.

251
00:18:44,359 --> 00:18:45,520
Alright...

252
00:18:45,880 --> 00:18:48,360
I'll be there in ten minutes.

253
00:18:50,519 --> 00:18:52,040
Why, thank you.

254
00:19:11,119 --> 00:19:13,040
It's in the sixth street.

255
00:19:18,720 --> 00:19:20,240
Fourth...

256
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:25,120
The next one on the left.

257
00:19:39,880 --> 00:19:42,120
It's at the end of the impasse.

258
00:19:45,079 --> 00:19:47,360
You can park next to the white car.

259
00:19:55,279 --> 00:19:57,000
Can you open the door?

260
00:20:15,799 --> 00:20:17,640
Yes, hello.

261
00:20:18,039 --> 00:20:19,600
Is this the taxi driver?

262
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:21,440
Yes, I'm listening.

263
00:20:22,960 --> 00:20:27,560
I had an accident with my husband.
You brought us to the hospital.

264
00:20:27,759 --> 00:20:30,200
Yes, I recognized your voice.

265
00:20:30,480 --> 00:20:33,240
Have you changed your number?

266
00:20:34,640 --> 00:20:36,320
It's my husband's...

267
00:20:36,559 --> 00:20:40,680
I wanted to tell you
that I'm in town,

268
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:43,760
To come recover it.

269
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:45,800
Recover what?

270
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:48,240
The film, of course.

