45 tomans.

345
00:25:14,440 --> 00:25:16,840
I'll have The Big Bang Theory next week.

346
00:25:19,359 --> 00:25:20,360
Fine!

347
00:25:21,839 --> 00:25:23,480
Same time next week.

348
00:25:28,920 --> 00:25:31,080
Too bad you didn't come in, next time.

349
00:25:31,279 --> 00:25:32,320
Thank you.

350
00:25:33,960 --> 00:25:35,600
Goodbye, good luck.

351
00:25:43,279 --> 00:25:45,120
Since when are we associates?

352
00:26:07,319 --> 00:26:08,840
ANNOUNCER: "Door not closed."

353
00:26:11,400 --> 00:26:12,720
This is not mine.

354
00:26:14,680 --> 00:26:16,880
Take us with you, please.

355
00:26:17,079 --> 00:26:20,000
We're late, our taxi didn't arrive.

356
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:21,760
Where are you going?

357
00:26:22,720 --> 00:26:23,560
Cheshmeh Ali.

358
00:26:23,799 --> 00:26:25,120
Cheshmeh Ali...

359
00:26:26,920 --> 00:26:29,840
- We're late.
- It's not on our way!

360
00:26:30,039 --> 00:26:31,160
We haven't asked you.

361
00:26:31,359 --> 00:26:32,480
Please, sir.

362
00:26:32,680 --> 00:26:34,520
We have to be there at twelve.

363
00:26:35,160 --> 00:26:36,240
Please take us. 

364
00:26:36,440 --> 00:26:39,960
I will take you there.
This gentleman is getting out further on.

365
00:26:40,160 --> 00:26:40,840
One moment.

366
00:26:42,559 --> 00:26:45,000
Go to the other side.
Let me grab my bag.

367
00:26:52,599 --> 00:26:54,320
I hope we'll be on time.

368
00:27:04,559 --> 00:27:05,880
Move over a little.

369
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:10,240
Be careful not to spill any water.

370
00:27:13,920 --> 00:27:16,640
Be glad that we ran into this.
You're always groaning.

371
00:27:16,839 --> 00:27:18,120
And if we don't arrive in time?

372
00:27:18,319 --> 00:27:21,520
Of course we will.
Why wouldn't we make it?

373
00:27:23,160 --> 00:27:24,760
I assure you...

374
00:27:24,960 --> 00:27:27,600
That I didn't want to tell him that.

375
00:27:28,079 --> 00:27:30,560
But usually, he buys around 3 films.

376
00:27:31,200 --> 00:27:33,440
This time he took everything.

377
00:27:33,640 --> 00:27:35,440
And that's because of you.

378
00:27:36,079 --> 00:27:38,880
If you go with me to see my clients,

379
00:27:39,720 --> 00:27:41,800
We'll bring the house down!

380
00:27:42,599 --> 00:27:44,240
As a partner, then?

381
00:27:45,960 --> 00:27:48,640
It's a cultural activity, what I do.

382
00:27:49,519 --> 00:27:51,600
These films do not come out in Iran.

383
00:27:51,799 --> 00:27:54,200
How can these college student
see them otherwise?

384
00:27:55,440 --> 00:27:57,160
Your son, for example.

385
00:27:57,759 --> 00:27:59,040
And even you!

386
00:27:59,640 --> 00:28:01,720
Without me, adieu Woody Allen!

387
00:28:05,480 --> 00:28:06,960
It's just as at home.

388
00:28:07,160 --> 00:28:10,120
I tell him: "Why do you lock yourself in the bathroom?"

389
00:28:10,319 --> 00:28:13,160
Who is risking to come watch
your dream body?

390
00:28:15,160 --> 00:28:17,920
You're much too relaxed.

391
00:28:18,119 --> 00:28:22,120
When you're this calm,
it necessarily irritates the others.

392
00:28:22,839 --> 00:28:24,760
- You're speaking about yourself?
- Of course.

393
00:28:24,960 --> 00:28:27,440
You're always on edge.
I'm normal at least.

394
00:28:27,640 --> 00:28:30,080
I'm fine just as I am.

395
00:28:31,319 --> 00:28:34,680
My friend, I will ask you
to get out over there.

396
00:28:42,400 --> 00:28:43,080
There?

397
00:28:43,279 --> 00:28:46,240
Yes, you can find another taxi.

398
00:28:50,200 --> 00:28:51,720
How much do I owe you?

399
00:28:53,160 --> 00:28:56,280
Save it for your cultural activities,
it's okay.

400
00:29:01,039 --> 00:29:03,120
- It's closed.
- I'll open it.

401
00:29:14,160 --> 00:29:16,240
He won't let go.

402
00:29:17,480 --> 00:29:18,600
M. Panahi...

403
00:29:18,799 --> 00:29:21,680
I assure you, I wanted 
to help you.

404
00:29:22,079 --> 00:29:24,840
I did not mean to disrespect you.

405
00:29:25,039 --> 00:29:26,880
I meant no harm.

406
00:29:27,440 --> 00:29:29,520
Thank you, goodbye.

407
00:29:34,759 --> 00:29:37,600
The time on the display is correct?

408
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:39,320
Let's see...

409
00:29:44,400 --> 00:29:46,680
It's delayed by a few minutes.

410
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:49,160
When will we be at Cheshmeh Ali ?

411
00:29:49,599 --> 00:29:53,440
It depends on the traffic.

412
00:29:54,240 --> 00:29:56,960
Will we be there before twelve?

413
00:29:57,160 --> 00:29:58,400
I hope so.

414
00:29:58,599 --> 00:30:01,760
Even if there is traffic?

415
00:30:02,480 --> 00:30:04,000
I don't know.

416
00:30:05,039 --> 00:30:07,840
Accelerate and we'll be there in time,
God willing.

417
00:30:08,119 --> 00:30:11,000
God willing? And then what?

418
00:30:11,200 --> 00:30:13,720
We have to be there before twelve!

419
00:30:14,759 --> 00:30:16,320
Excusez-moi...

420
00:30:29,119 --> 00:30:31,840
People often go there in the afternoon,
why the hurry?

421
00:30:32,039 --> 00:30:35,240
We're not going for fun, 
it's very serious.

422
00:30:35,480 --> 00:30:38,120
We must throw these fish into
the fountain at twelve precisely.

423
00:30:38,319 --> 00:30:40,080
You don't seem to understand.

424
00:30:40,279 --> 00:30:42,000
Our lives depend on it.

425
00:30:42,359 --> 00:30:44,240
In the water at twelve, exact!

426
00:30:44,440 --> 00:30:46,560
A matter of life and death.

427
00:30:58,440 --> 00:31:00,520
The fish, they will die.

428
00:31:02,400 --> 00:31:04,440
Sir, hurry!

429
00:31:06,640 --> 00:31:09,680
Faster, they'll die.

430
00:31:12,680 --> 00:31:13,760
ll va m'achever.

431
00:31:15,559 --> 00:31:17,080
Hurry, they're going to die!

432
00:31:17,279 --> 00:31:18,880
Lift your foot.

433
00:31:19,920 --> 00:31:21,040
They're dying.

434
00:31:22,359 --> 00:31:23,520
Don't crush them.

435
00:31:23,720 --> 00:31:25,640
Faster.

436
00:31:28,599 --> 00:31:29,600
Go ahead, pour!

437
00:31:31,440 --> 00:31:33,600
Quickly, put the fish in.

438
00:31:33,799 --> 00:31:34,960
There's enough water!

439
00:31:35,160 --> 00:31:36,800
Everything's fine.

440
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:38,640
A minute.

441
00:31:39,359 --> 00:31:40,800
Is it dead?

442
00:31:44,279 --> 00:31:45,760
A moment.

443
00:31:51,160 --> 00:31:52,920
Pick up the pieces of glass.

444
00:32:03,240 --> 00:32:05,520
He's just standing there watching us.

445
00:32:06,440 --> 00:32:08,000
It's nothing.

446
00:32:08,799 --> 00:32:10,440
The fish are fine.

447
00:32:12,319 --> 00:32:13,720
Okay.

448
00:32:23,039 --> 00:32:25,800
I beg your pardon, I'm sorry.

449
00:32:41,319 --> 00:32:45,600
ANNOUNCER: "The number you called cannot
be reached, please try again later."

450
00:32:47,079 --> 00:32:49,160
- Aren't they hurt?
- No.

451
00:32:51,960 --> 00:32:53,360
I am really sorry.

452
00:32:53,559 --> 00:32:57,520
I listened to you and I got distracted.

453
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:01,480
Why do ordinary fish
matter this much to you?

454
00:33:02,000 --> 00:33:03,840
They aren't ordinary at all!

455
00:33:04,039 --> 00:33:07,080
We've taken care of them for a year.

456
00:33:07,319 --> 00:33:11,560
And after a year, you put
them back into the water?

457
00:33:12,160 --> 00:33:14,120
Haven't you understood?

458
00:33:14,440 --> 00:33:16,200
It's very simple.

459
00:33:16,480 --> 00:33:19,120
We took them from the well of Chesmeh Ali.

460
00:33:19,319 --> 00:33:21,800
We have been born five years apart,

461
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:24,120
but both at noon.

462
00:33:25,079 --> 00:33:28,240
So, we have to put them into
the water at noon,

463
00:33:28,480 --> 00:33:32,560
and take two new ones. Otherwise,
it's the end of us.

464
00:33:32,759 --> 00:33:35,160
Dead, gone! Do you understand?

465
00:33:35,799 --> 00:33:37,160
Do not talk about misfortune.

466
00:33:37,359 --> 00:33:39,240
It's twelve or death.

467
00:33:40,119 --> 00:33:42,440
Pardon me, I have to make a call.

468
00:33:53,279 --> 00:33:56,480
I'll drop you off after the bridge.

469
00:33:56,680 --> 00:33:59,440
I'll find you another cab.
He'll be faster.

470
00:33:59,640 --> 00:34:01,520
We absolutely must...

471
00:34:01,720 --> 00:34:04,960
Because I'll have to pick up
my niece from school.

472
00:34:05,160 --> 00:34:06,920
Please, bring us!

473
00:34:07,119 --> 00:34:09,000
We have to be there at twelve!

474
00:34:09,920 --> 00:34:14,200
I would've liked to,
but she cannot go home alone.

475
00:34:17,119 --> 00:34:19,760
We will never make it in time!

476
00:34:20,639 --> 00:34:23,400
- What is he doing?
- No idea.

477
00:34:26,760 --> 00:34:29,520
To hell with this incompetence.

478
00:34:29,760 --> 00:34:32,520
He drives like a donky
and moreover, he is lost.

479
00:34:33,159 --> 00:34:34,400
What is he doing?

480
00:34:34,599 --> 00:34:35,880
I don't know at all.

481
00:34:38,119 --> 00:34:40,200
Have mercy, we won't make it otherwise.

482
00:34:40,400 --> 00:34:43,840
He knows the way, it will go faster.

483
00:34:44,280 --> 00:34:46,880
We'll never be there at twelve.

484
00:34:48,920 --> 00:34:50,720
I'm sorry.

485
00:34:51,480 --> 00:34:53,080
What a moron!

486
00:35:01,280 --> 00:35:02,760
Thank you, goodbye.

487
00:36:37,639 --> 00:36:40,320
You've come to pick me up
in this heap of garbage?

488
00:36:40,519 --> 00:36:43,400
I've told everyone that
my uncle is a CEO!

489
00:36:43,599 --> 00:36:47,760
They're going to say I'm a liar!
Think of my reputation!

490
00:36:47,960 --> 00:36:50,040
You talk to me about discipline,

491
00:36:50,239 --> 00:36:52,760
And you left me hanging around for an hour.

492
00:36:53,400 --> 00:36:56,160
And there you are, bluntly staring at me.

493
00:36:56,440 --> 00:36:57,920
I'm sorry, young lady.

494
00:36:59,199 --> 00:37:00,480
By the way, hello.

495
00:37:01,119 --> 00:37:03,440
Hello, don't change the subject.

496
00:37:03,639 --> 00:37:06,240
What would you have done
if somebody abducted me?

497
00:37:06,559 --> 00:37:08,360
T'inquiète, ça risque pas d'arriver.
Don't worry, I don't believe that would happen.

498
00:37:09,199 --> 00:37:11,600
Nobody would have the nerve to do that.

499
00:37:11,840 --> 00:37:12,520
Enter.

500
00:37:12,760 --> 00:37:15,960
I have an appointment with an old friend.

501
00:37:16,159 --> 00:37:19,680
And your pretty niece,
is she worth nothing?

502
00:37:19,880 --> 00:37:23,080
I'll go.
I'll leave you to your appointment.

503
00:37:23,280 --> 00:37:27,280
I'll find my way, like
the girl in The Mirror.

504
00:37:28,199 --> 00:37:30,600
Am I going or not going?

505
00:37:31,079 --> 00:37:32,480
As you wish.

506
00:37:32,679 --> 00:37:35,840
You're defintely not funny.
It was such a joy for me to see you.

507
00:37:36,039 --> 00:37:39,000
You arrive too late and now you go on, too bad!

508
00:37:39,360 --> 00:37:42,600
I've already said I'm sorry.
Why are you making such a scene?

509
00:37:44,320 --> 00:37:45,760
I'm joking.

510
00:37:45,960 --> 00:37:49,320
If I would've wanted to leave,
I wouldn't have waited.

511
00:37:49,679 --> 00:37:52,000
Why did you turn off your cellphone?

512
00:37:52,320 --> 00:37:53,640
Should I tell you the truth?

513
00:37:54,599 --> 00:37:56,720
If you're capable of that for once.

514
00:37:56,920 --> 00:37:59,640
When have I ever lied to you.

515
00:37:59,840 --> 00:38:01,320
Go on, I'm listening.

516
00:38:03,239 --> 00:38:06,800
I was sure you were going to call
me with lots of excuses

517
00:38:07,000 --> 00:38:09,240
not to pick me up.

518
00:38:10,920 --> 00:38:12,480
And what if I would've been worried?

519
00:38:12,679 --> 00:38:13,800
I do like mom.

520
00:38:14,159 --> 00:38:17,360
When you forget her,
she pretends to be sick...

521
00:38:17,559 --> 00:38:21,880
And she doesn't reply to your calls.
You disembark all the time!

522
00:38:44,519 --> 00:38:45,520
Hello, how are you?

523
00:38:47,880 --> 00:38:50,040
It's me, Panahi.

524
00:38:50,559 --> 00:38:53,440
I'm very sorry for the dalay.

525
00:38:55,719 --> 00:38:58,080
No, I'm coming.

526
00:39:03,719 --> 00:39:05,880
Where are you?

527
00:39:11,280 --> 00:39:14,840
Stay there,
I'll be there in a few minutes.

528
00:39:15,039 --> 00:39:16,840
Stay there and wait for me.

529
00:39:18,000 --> 00:39:20,040
I'll be there any moment now.

530
00:39:22,280 --> 00:39:25,560
Did he think you were
going to let him down?

531
00:39:25,760 --> 00:39:27,000
Never mind.

532
00:39:29,360 --> 00:39:31,240
So, what did you want to talk about?

533
00:39:31,440 --> 00:39:33,560
Not while we're driving.

534
00:39:33,760 --> 00:39:37,160
Why not? We can discuss.

535
00:39:37,360 --> 00:39:39,960
You're impossible, my poor uncle.

536
00:39:40,159 --> 00:39:43,920
When you're out with a lady
as distinguished and cultivates as I,

537
